b"[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](sbe48545.htm)  [Next](sbe48547.htm)\n\n* * *\n\n10\\. And on account of Sm _ri_ ti.\n\nThis follows from Sm _ri_ ti also, which declares 'when the pralaya has come\nand the end of the Highest, they all together with Brahman enter the highest\nplace.'--For all these reasons Badari holds that the troop of the conducting\ndeities, beginning with Light, leads the souls of those only who meditate on\nthe effected Brahman, i e. Hira _n_ yagarbha.\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: 11. The Highest ... on account of primariness of meaning](sbe48547.htm)\n\n"